Fuller and on off, this is defended towards point.
On a good length and straight on the stumps, Tom Blundell defends it back towards the bowler.
FOUR! Fuller and outside off, Tom Blundell bends his back knee and drives it through covers for a boundary. Oh, it's a no ball as well. Five runs off this ball.
On middle, blocked out.

Shout for an appeal! The typical 'celebrappeal' of Stuart Board but the finger stays down. Inswinger, on a length and around off, Daryl Mitchell tries to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads. Stokes has strong ears, he has heard that and hence is confident that there is no need to take the DRS.
Back of a length and outside off, Daryl Mitchell shoulders arms.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.

Broad goes wide of the crease and serves a length ball around middle and leg, Mitchell nudges it down to fine leg. The fielder there runs across to his right and puts in a dive to stop it from touching the fence. The umpire gets it checked upstairs and the replays find everything fine. Two runs taken.
Around off, on a length, Daryl Mitchell defends it solidly.
Lands it on a length and outside off, holding its line Daryl strides forward and leaves.
Fuller and on middle, Tom Blundell defends it towards square leg.
Digs it in short, around off and there is some steep bounce. Blundell swivels and pulls, keeping it down intentionally but finds square leg.
Quite wide outside off, on a length, Blundell shoulders arms.
Fuller and on middle, Tom Blundell defends it towards square leg.
Outside off, Tom Blundell eases it on the off side.
Shorter one on leg, Tom Blundell leaves it alone towards the keeper.
On a length and outside off, Daryl Mitchell looks to block it but misses.
Similar to the last delivery, Daryl Mitchell guards his stumps and lets it go towards the keeper.
On a good length and outside off, Daryl Mitchell guides it towards point and rotates the strike.
Good-length delivery and on middle, Tom Blundell flicks it towards square leg.
On a good length and on off, Tom Blundell stays in his crease and blocks it away.
Back of a length and outside off, Tom Blundell jumps a bit and defends it back towards James Anderson.
Length ball on off, swinging away, Daryl Mitchell guides it towards point.
On a length and outside off, Daryl Mitchell lets it go towards the keeper.

FOUR! This is very well played by Daryl Mitchell. Shorter one on middle, Daryl Mitchell plays a hook shot towards backward square leg. The fielder there gave it a good try diving to his right but couldn't get the ball. The ball races behind the fence for a boundary.
Length ball on off, this is defended towards covers.
Surprise yorker from Ben Stokes, Daryl Mitchell fumbles a bit but manages to block it in the end.
Fuller and outside off, driven towards covers for one.
On middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.

JUST WIDE AND FOUR! Almost! The extravagant shot got about a wicket. Fuller and on off, this shapes away. Daryl goes for a big one down the ground. This goes off the outside edge past the diving gully fielder and into the third man fence.
BEATEN! Another expansive stroke! Fuller and on off, shapes away late. Mitchell looks to go down the ground again but misses. He is looking to attack Anderson.
Touch fuller and on leg, Daryl Mitchell flicks it towards mid-wicket for one.
Good-length delivery on middle, Tom Blundell blocks it out solidly.
Back of a length and outside off, Tom Blundell guides it straight towards the fielder at point.
Goes fuller and outside off, this is eased towards the mid off region.
Outside off, Daryl Mitchell drives it into the gap at covers and gets a brace.
Fuller and outside off, Daryl Mitchell eases it towards covers for one.
Length ball down the leg side, Tom Blundell flicks it towards mid-wicket and takes a quick single.
FOUR! Fuller and straight in the line of the stumps, Daryl Mitchell flicks it through square leg for a boundary.

FOUR! Back to back boundaries from Daryl Mitchell. Fuller and outside off, Daryl Mitchell drives it straight and straight past Ben Stokes. The ball races towards long off for a boundary. This was well timed from Daryl Mitchell.
Tossed up on off, lands it well. Defended.
Another one, nicely tossed up. Blocked out.
Pushes this one through and on off, this is played with a straight bat.
Tossed up outside off with a hint of spin, Tom Blundell blocks it on the off side.
Tossed-up delivery on middle, Tom Blundell flicks it towards square leg for one.
Flighted up, giving it some air and landing outside off, Daryl Mitchell leaves it alone.
That is a good leave on this wicket. A brave one we should say. This lands just around off. It goes on with the angle. Blundell lets it be.
This is a lot wider outside off. Easy leave for the batsman.
Two! Batting seems a lot easier now! On the pads, this is worked through mid-wicket for two.
Shortish and on off, this is pushed to covers.
Two more to end the over! On off, this is pushed through covers for a couple.
A single to end! On off, this is pushed to cover for one.
Flighted and full, outside off, Tom advances down the track but mistimes his drive to mid off.
Tossed up, around off, Blundell plays yet another false drive as it goes off the inner half to the leg side.
Tom steps out, and the ball dips at the very end. He looks to drive but it goes off the inner half back to the bowler.
On middle, defended.
On middle, short. Gets away with it as it is only pulled for one to deep mid-wicket.
Floats it up on middle, Daryl Mitchell defends it back.
That could have been close! Tom would have in though. On off, shorter, this is pushed towards cover. He takes off. The fielder has a shy but misses at the bowler's end.
Back of a length and on off, blocked.
Yet another delivery on off, defended.
On the stumps, Mitchell plays it back to the bowler.

Frustrating runs for England! Fuller and on off, this one moves away. Mitchell looks to drive, it goes off the outside edge past the diving backward point fielder who does get a hand to it. Two taken.
On off, defended.
Extra flight on this one, around middle, Tom Blundell gives the charge to take it on the full and pushes it to mid on.
Flighted again, full and around leg, this time Blundell moves back and works it to square leg for a run.
Delivers it very full in length, around leg, Mitchell knocks it down to long on for one.
Loopy and full, around off, Tom walks forward and drives it back to the bowler.
Drags his length short and lands it close to off, Tom Blundell this time goes on the back foot and punches it towards mid on.
Another half-tracker from the leggie, around middle, Tom moves back and wrists it through square leg for a single.
Anderson bowls it on a length, around middle and leg, Tom Blundell gets back and tucks it through square leg for a couple of runs.
Fraction short and wide outside off, Tom stays back and punches it square of the wicket on the off side for a couple again. The 50-run stand comes up! Lead is 98.

Superb delivery and it stays a touch low as well. Angling in around off, on a length and keeping low. Blundell keeps his eyes glued to the ball and defends it from the toe end of the bat. Had he missed, he would have been dead plumb in front.
Gets behind the line of the delivery and defends it solidly to the off side.
Fuller and around off, Tom Blundell presses forward and pushes it back in the direction of the bowler.

FOUR! Poor line and punished! Fuller in length and around leg, Tom Blundell picks it off his pads and whips it down to fine leg. The fielder dives near the fence but fails to cut it off. The runs have started to flow on the other side of the Drinks break. Lead crosses 100!
A freebie. Full toss outside off, Daryl Mitchell walks down the track and smashes it down the ground. It is retrieved before the long on fence, only a run is taken.
Loopy and full, around off, Tom Blundell strides forward and blocks it safely.
Matt Parkinson goes short and on off, Tom moves back and punches it to short mid-wicket.
Uses his feet to reach the pitch of the ball and strokes it back to the bowler.
Floated and full, around middle, Tom Blundell lunges and brings his bat down in time to defend it away. It goes off the inner edge to square leg.
A long hop down the leg side, Blundell steps back and hits it down to fine leg for three runs.
Play and a miss! Short in length and wide outside off, Tom loses concentration and tries to cut it through the line wiildly but misses.
Around off, defended back.
A touch short and on off, Tom gets back and forces it to mid on. 'Wait on' is the shout from Blundell.
This one is on a driving length outside off, Tom Blundell regains his composure and allows it through to the keeper.
Gentle delivery, on a length and wide outside off, Tom Blundell looks to go after it initially but then restrains himself.
Lands it on a good length and outside off, Tom stays back and looks to leave. It though takes his bat and goes rolling towards the slip cordon.
Floated delivery, above the eye line of the batter as it dips on a fuller length around off, Daryl Mitchell drives it towards mid off.
Quicker and fuller on middle, pushed down to deepish mid on for a run.
FOUR! That's drilled! Matt Parkinson senses the charge perhaps and tries to bowl it wide outside off. It turns out to be a low full toss though and Tom Blundell hammers it to the cover fence.
Slightly short and on middle, Tom Blundell goes back and drags his pull shot to deep mid-wicket for a run.
Fullish and around off, defended off the front foot.

Fuller again, around middle, Daryl Mitchell softly works it in the direction of mid on. The mid-wicket fielder puts in a dive but fails to stop the ball, however, his attempt stopped the batters from going for a run.
Back of a length, around off, Blundell stays back and plays it down to point.
Delivers it on a length and outside off, Tom Blundell thrusts forward to cover his stumps and shoulders arms.
On a good length around off, angling in, Blundell defends it from the back foot to mid on.
Plenty of width there outside off, short in length and shaping away, Tom leaves it watchfully.

Edged but safe! Fuller and close to off, Blundell tries to defend near his front pad but it takes a soft outside edge. Foakes dives across to his right and partially stops the racing ball. Just a run.
Serves it on a length, around off, Daryl defends it to the off side.

Strikes the stumps at the other end! Full and flighted around off, Tom Blundell dances down the track and drills it straight back. Matt Parkinson tries to stop it but it brushes his fingers and goes on to collide with the stumps at the other end. Daryl Mitchell is alert and has his bat parked inside the crease.
Loopy and full, around off, defended off the front foot.
Slower through the air, full again and around off, this time Blundell shimmies down a bit and then blocks.
Quicker and shorter, around leg, Tom moves back and works it behind square leg for a brace.
Quicker again, short and on middle, punched from the back foot to short mid-wicket.
FOUR! Bang! Poor length from the leggie. Short and wide outside off, turning away, Tom Blundell rocks back and whacks it to sweeper cover for a boundary. That will be Tea on Day 2!
Starts with a length ball, around off and angling in, Mitchell defends it from the back foot to mid on.
Slightly short in length, Daryl uses the angle of the bowler and helps it to square leg for a run.
Serves it on a length and outside off, Tom takes a positive stride forward before making a leave.

EDGY FOUR! Potts delivers it full and outside off, Blundell gets on the front foot and goes for a full-blooded cover drive. It though takes the outside edge and runs wide of the gully fielder for a boundary.
FOUR! This time it is a controlled pull shot. Short in length and outside off, Tom Blundell swivels on the back foot and pulls it with authority to the deep mid-wicket fence.
Back of a length, on top of off, Tom defends it from the back foot. 9 from the first over after Tea!
Begins with a length delivery around off, angling in, Daryl Mitchell gets on the front foot and defends it towards mid off.
Full and on off, angling in again, Daryl Mitchell flicks it off the inner half to deep square leg for one.
Shortish and outside off, Blundell picks the length early, goes on the back foot and defends it solidly to the off side.
Lands it on a length and outside off, Tom drives it past the left side of the cover-point fielder and collects a run. Moves to 48!
Broad keeps his line around off, it drops on a length and gets blocked by Daryl.
Fuller on this occasion, outside off, Daryl Mitchell drives but picks out the cover fielder.
Back of a length, around off, Blundell goes on the back foot and punches it to the right of the cover fielder. He dives to make a partial stop and the batters decide not to risk a run.
Quite wide outside off, on a good length, Tom Blundell has nothing to do with it.
Fuller this time, outside off and inviting the driving, Tom Blundell is not lured into it.
Gets behind the line of the delivery and blocks it solidly from the back foot.
Beauty from Potts! Gets a length ball to straighten a hint after landing outside off, Tom Blundell feels for it and gets beaten.
Fuller and on middle and leg, Blundell fails to flick and it goes off his pads to backward square leg. A stifled appeal for an lbw from the English players as the batters cross. Missing leg.
Length ball on leg, this is defended out solidly.
Goes fuller this time, Tom Blundell eases it towards mid off.
Good-length delivery down the middle, Tom Blundell defends it towards mid off.
Outside off, Tom Blundell blocks it out towards the point region.
On a good length and on middle, Tom Blundell tries to block it but gets a thick inside edge. The ball rolls towards the vacant short leg region.
On middle, Tom Blundell looks to block it but gets an inside edge again, the ball rolls towards square leg. A maiden over from Stuart Broad.
Length ball on middle, this is defended out.
Touch fuller and on middle, Daryl Mitchell tries to play it but gets a thick inside edge as the ball races towards deep square leg. A couple of runs taken.
Outside off, Daryl Mitchell gets in two minds but puts his bat in the end. The ball goes straight towards the fielder at slips.
Fuller and on middle, this is defended towards the mid off region.

That just does not bounce! Length and outside off, this one goes underneath the bat as Daryl looks to push at it. It hits the pad of Foakes and deflects wide of Bairstow at third slip. The batters spot an opportunity and steal a bye.
Shorter and outside off, this stays low again. Tom looks to cut but misses.
Length ball on leg, Daryl Mitchell flicks it towards mid-wicket for a brace.
Shorter one on middle, Daryl Mitchell ducks under it.
Another shorter one on middle, Daryl Mitchell lets it go.
Angled into the middle pole, DM pushes it to mid on.

NOT OUT! Daryl Mitchell is in! He was sent back just at the right time! On off, this is pushed towards cover. Mitchell takes off. He is sent back though. He turns and looks to head back. The fielder picks the ball up and hits the stumps at the keeper's end. It is taken upstairs. Replays show that Mitchell is in.
Shorter and outside off, Mitchell slashes but misses.
Down the leg side, Blundell looks to flick but misses.
On middle, defended.
On the stumps, kept out.

FOUR! Fifty for Tom Blundell! This has been a lovely inning from him. He has looked very assured and has made full use of the good batting conditions at the moment. Needs to go on, a big score is on offer. Gets there with a lovely square drive. This is full and outside off, it is hit through point for a boundary.
Back of a length and on off, blocked.
Length ball outside off, Tom Blundell raises arms and lets it through towards the keeper.
Shorter one on leg, Daryl Mitchell ducks under it.
Outside off, Daryl Mitchell defends it towards the mid off region.
Length ball outside off, Daryl Mitchell doesn't bother it and lets it go.

Fifty for Mitchell now! Another good inning and a much-needed one for his side. He too would know the job is not done. Needs to make it into a big one. This is on the pads, he flicks it through square leg for one.
Touch fuller outside off, Tom Blundell shoulders arms to it and lets it through towards the keeper.
Fuller and on leg, Tom Blundell defends it towards mid on.
Good-length delivery outside off, Daryl Mitchell defends it towards the mid off region.
Outside off again, Daryl Mitchell lets it go.
Similar to the last delivery, Daryl Mitchell again lets it go towards the keeper.
Length ball on off, Daryl Mitchell defends it to covers.
Length ball outside off, Daryl Mitchell doesn't bother playing at it.
A maiden over from James Anderson. On a good length and outside off, Daryl Mitchell lets it through towards the keeper.
Two! Fuller and outside off, this is guided through point for a couple.
Angled into the pads, this is worked to square leg.
Half an appeal and turned down! Angled into the pads, Tom Blundell looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. Going down leg.
FOUR! Uppish but safe! Full and on the pads, Tom Blundell flicks it stylishly between mid-wicket and square leg for a boundary. The century stand comes up!
On middle, Tom Blundell blocks it out.
Slightly fuller and on off, Tom Blundell pushes it to mid off.
Outside off, left alone.
That is a beauty! Angled into the off pole, this lands and then moves away. Mitchell is beaten as he tries to defend.
Good length and on off, defended.
Yet another one on a length and on off, this is pushed to covers.
On the stumps, kept out.
Back of a length and on middle, kept out.
Bangs it short, comes very slowly off the surface. Blundell looks to pull but it goes off the toe-end toward wide of mid on.
Shorter again, this is hit through square leg for one. So one thing is for sure, Tom Blundell will take on the challenge of playing the pull shot.
Mitchell though is happy to evade it. Short and on middle, he ducks.
Another short one, this time, Mitchell looks to pull. He connects well but the ball hits Ollie Pope at short leg.
Just over! Lucky escape! The ploy to bowl short almost works! On middle, Mitchell looks to pull. It gets big on him, and goes off the splice but just over Broad at mid on. A run is taken.
Another short one on middle, Blundell is in total control of the pull shot, and it goes through mid-wicket for one.
Good length and on off, kept out.
Good length and outside off, left alone.
Another one wide outside off, not played at.
Gets this one to tail back in nicely. This is worked to mid-wicket.
The away swinger this time, not played at.
This one shapes away from outside off, Tom Blundell does not fiddle with it.
Way too short, Mitchell looked to pull but after seeing the bounce, he bails out.
FOUR! Uppish but just wide again! Short and on middle, Daryl Mitchell goes for the pull, once again it goes more off the splice, wide of the fielder at mid on and into the boundary.
A short one, this time Mitchell pulls it nicely towards deep square leg for one.
Another short one, on middle, this is hit through square leg for one again.
FOUR! That is a powerful pull shot! Short and on middle, Daryl Mitchell stays back and hammers the pull, it goes through the gap between square leg and fine leg for a boundary.
Goes fuller now and on middle, defended.
Back of a length, around off, the batter blocks it from the back foot.
Short in length and outside off, stroked to point for a single.
Around off, on a length, blocked.
Pitches it up and outside off, DM drives but finds the cover fielder.
Jimmy sticks to his line around off and serves it on a good length, Daryl defends it from the back foot.
Well stopped! Fuller again, outside off, Daryl Mitchell drives it from the toe end of his bat to covers where Ben Stokes dives across to his right to stop the racing ball.
A wayward bouncer, way down the leg side, Tom leaves it.
Short in length, around middle and leg, Blundell pulls it down to fine leg for one.
Fractionally short and down the leg side, Mitchell tries to glance but gets a thin inside edge. It races down to fine leg and they gather a couple of runs.
Digs it in short, around leg, Mitchell stands tall and pulls it to deep backward square leg for a run.
Change in line from Stokes. He serves it on a length and angles it outside off. Blundell leaves it. Ben Foakes is expecting the line to be around leg and has to dive to his right to collect the ball.
Fuller and down the leg side, Blundell fails to flick and it goes behind off his pads. This time Foakes dives across to his left to stop the ball.
FOUR! Down the slope! Anderson serves it on a good length and outside off, Daryl Mitchell pushes inside the line and edges it wide of the slip cordon. It scoots away to the fence in no time.
The batter has just watchfully blocked this out.
Keeps it on a length and around off, Daryl Mitchell shoulders arms.

FOUR! Great placement to earn the second boundary in this over. Anderson errs in line and delivers a full ball on middle and leg, Daryl Mitchell waits for it and whips it through mid-wicket for a boundary. Lead is 173 now.
Too full and wide outside off, Mitchell drives it to wide mid off.

FOUR! Gorgeous! Make it three boundaries in the over. Frustration for Anderson and England. An overpitched delivery, around off, Mitchell shows the full face of the bat and caresses it down the ground, past mid on and it races away.
Ouch! A cross-seamer from Stokes. Digs it in short and there is some steep bounce around middle, Blundell tries to work it across but gets hit on the gloves.
Wide! Wayward bouncer again, way down the leg side, it's left alone.
Short in length and drifting down the leg side, Tom Blundell tries to pull but it goes below his bat and disappears into the gloves of Ben Foakes.
On a good length around off, defended off the back foot.
There is movement. Big inswinger from Big Ben. It starts from outside off and jags back in from a good length. Tom Blundell tries to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Short and down the leg side again, Tom tries to pull but misses.
Stokes continues to bang it in short, around middle and leg, Blundell connects this time with his pull shot and sends it to deep backward square leg for a run.
Starts with a length ball on off, Blundell defends it from the back foot to short mid-wicket.
Broad serves it wide outside off on this occasion, Tom Blundell plants his front foot forward and makes a leave.
Fullish and around off, angling in, Tom pushes it down towards mid on.

FOUR! Top shot! A bit aerial but Blundell knew what he was doing! Broad offers width outside off, it's on a length and Tom Blundell drives it on the up through the vacant cover-point region. Lead is 183.
In the zone outside off, Tom shoulders arms.
FOUR! That's bread and butter for a set batter. Short in length and wide outside off, Tom Blundell eases himself on the back foot and cuts it firmly through point for a boundary.
Starts with a short ball down the leg side, Mitchell flicks but finds short fine leg.
Mishit! Flighted and full, around leg, Daryl dances down the track to heave it over the leg side but ends up getting an inside edge. It squirts to deep square leg and they get a couple.
Floated and full, around middle, defended.
Flighted and on off, defended again.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
Fuller and on off, Daryl draws forward and defends.
Back of a length, around off, Tom turns and places it in front of square leg for one.
In the channel outside off, on a length and holding its line, Mitchell covers his stumps and shoulders arms.
Angles in a length ball, around off, Daryl defends it from the back foot to short mid-wicket.
Fuller in length and outside off, moving away late off the seam, Daryl Mitchell allows it through.
Slants in a length ball on off, DM gets behind the line and blocks it down on the surface.
Short in length and outside off, Mitchell goes on his toes and defends it to the off side.
Flighted one, full and around off, Tom decides to hang on the back foot in defense.
Fuller and around off, Blundell steps down the track and defends it on the leg side.
Fails to put it away! A wide full toss outside off, Blundell skips down the track and smashes it to covers. Finds Stokes.
FOUR! Fine shot! 200 comes up for New Zealand. Flighted delivery, landing full around middle, Tom Blundell dances down the track and forces it to the long on fence.
Full and floated, on off, defended off the front foot.
Flighted again, full and on middle, Tom walks down the track and knocks it down to mid on. Finds the fielder.
Bowls it on a good length outside off, Mitchell blocks it from the back foot.
Shortish and on off, punched off the back foot to covers.
Keeps it on and around off, on a good length, Daryl is solid in his defense.
Full and going down the leg side, Mitchell clips it down to long leg where the fielder makes a sliding stop. Two runs taken.
A gentle outswinger, in the region outside off, Daryl shoulders arms.
On a length around middle, it's defended on the leg side.
Floated and around off, drifting in and spinning away a shade, Tom is forward in defense.
Jumps down the track to take it on the full and flicks it to mid-wicket. The fielder fumbles and they get a single. The stand moves to 150!
On the pads, tickled to deep square leg for one.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Blundell lunges and defends it down.
Too full and on middle, Tom comes down the track but gets too close to the line. Mishits his shot to mid on.
Loopy and full, around off, Blundell presses forward and defends it from the inner half of his blade.
Serves it on a length and close to off, Daryl Mitchell defends it from the crease.
Drifting down the leg side, Daryl Mitchell deflects it off his pads to fine leg. The fielder makes a diving stop near the fence to save one run. The lead crosses 200!
Back of a length on middle, Blundell moves back inside the crease and turns it in front of square leg for a single.
Arrows a full ball around leg, Mitchell plays it ahead of his pads and nudges it to mid-wicket.
Shortish and close to off, Daryl Mitchell stays back and blocks it to the off side.
A harmless outswinger, on a length and outside off, Daryl Mitchell watches it closely and lets it be.
Flighted and full, on middle, pushed down to mid on.
Fuller and around off, Tom walks forward and drives it with the spin to covers.
Googly around off, on the shorter side, Tom moves back and pushes it away again towards mid on.
Slightly short and on leg, Blundell hangs deep inside the crease and punches it towards mid on.
Uses his feet and bunts a full ball to mid off for a brisk run. Bairstow has a shy at the bowler's end but misses.
Floated and around middle, Daryl Mitchell gets forward to defend it with a straight blade but it catches the inside edge and runs down to fine leg. Two runs.
Flighted and around leg, helped to square leg.
Shout for an lbw, not given! Very full and around leg, Tom Blundell tries to sweep but misses. He is rapped on the pads, they appeal but it has perhaps landing outside leg.
Tossed up again, landing outside leg, Tom Blundell goes back to flick but misses and is hit on the thigh pad.
Down the leg side, tickled away to long leg for one.
Walks forward and knocks a full toss towards deepish mid on for a run.
A muted appeal again for an lbw. Fuller and landing outside leg, Tom tries to sweep but misses.
Outside off to begin with! Left alone.
On middle, this time gets it to straighten. Defended nicely.
Angled into middle, kept out.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
Fuller and on off, Daryl Mitchell strokes it to mid off.
On off, blocked.
Two more! On the pads, this is worked fine on the leg side for two.
Tossed up on off, defended.
On off, this is pushed to mid off.
Flighted ball on off, kept out.
Floats it up on off, kept out.
Another one on the stumps, defended.
On the stumps, defended well.
On off, kept out.
Another defensive stroke to this ball on middle.
Two more! Fuller and on middle, Daryl Mitchell strokes it down the ground, past mid on for two.
On the stumps, defended well.
On off, this is pushed to mid off.
Tom steps out, gets close to the pitch of the ball and hits it to mid off.
Tossed up on middle, kept out.
Shorter and on off, Tom Blundell pushes it through covers for one.
Flighted delivery on middle, defended.
Another one which is given air, it lands on middle, Daryl Mitchell reaches out for it and defends. Not a lot of turn or zip for Matt Parkinson too. The pitch seems to have gone really placid.
On the stumps, kept out.
Length ball on leg, Tom Blundell uses the pace of the bowler and flicks it towards backward square leg for a brace.
On a good length and on off, this is defended out solidly.
Length ball on middle, angling into the batter, Tom Blundell blocks this one out towards mid on.
Similar to the last delivery, Tom Blundell eases it towards the vacant short leg region.
On middle, Tom Blundell eases it towards point.
On a good length and on middle, Tom Blundell blocks it towards covers.
Tossed up outside off, Daryl Mitchell uses his feet and plays it towards mid off.
Flighted up on leg, Tom Blundell flicks this one towards backward square leg for a brace.
Tossed up outside off, Daryl Mitchell leaves it alone.
Fuller and on middle, Daryl Mitchell defends it back towards the bowler.
Floated up on leg, Daryl Mitchell flicks it towards square leg and rotates the strike.
Tossed up on off, this is defended back towards Matt Parkinson.
Length ball on middle and leg, Daryl Mitchell defends it towards the mid on region.
Fuller and on middle, Daryl Mitchell flicks it straight towards the fielder at mid-wicket.
Touch fuller and outside off, Daryl Mitchell shoulders arms to it.
Similar to the last delivery, Daryl Mitchell lets this one go as well. He is running in, good energy shown by Potts over here.
Change in line, this one is on middle, Daryl Mitchell defends it towards the mid on region.
Single off the last ball. Fuller and on middle, Daryl Mitchell flicks it towards square leg for one.
Tossed up on off, Daryl Mitchell eases it towards covers.
On middle, Daryl Mitchell flicks it towards square leg for one.
Touch fuller on middle with a hint of turn, Tom Blundell blocks this one out.
Fuller again and on middle, Tom Blundell eases it back towards Matt Parkinson.
FOUR! Flighted up on middle, Tom Blundell moves to his backfoot and flicks it through deep square leg for a boundary. He moves to 90.
On middle, this is flicked straight towards the fielder at short mid-wicket.
On off, defended out.
Length ball on off, Daryl Mitchell defends it back towards the bowler.
On a good length, quicker too, Daryl Mitchell blocks it towards covers.
Fuller on middle and leg, Daryl Mitchell puts his bat on it. The ball goes towards the cover region.
Outside off, this is defended towards the mid-wicket region.
FOUR! A boundary on the last ball of the day. Fuller and outside off, Daryl Mitchell drives it through long off for a boundary. He moves to 97. THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 2.
Solid from Tom Blundell! Good length and on off, Tom defends it onto the ground.
Just outside off, length delivery. Left alone.
Solid yet again! On a length and around off, kept out.
First runs of the day and it ocmes off the bat of Tom! Fuller and on off, this is pushed through covers for three.

THERE IT IS! 100 for Daryl Mitchell! Only his second in Tests. He was three runs away and the first ball he faced on Day 3, gets to the milestone. Outstanding knock. Talk about grabbing the opportunity. He probably got into the XI as Nicholls was not available and what a statement he has made. A ton when his team were in deep trouble. He is absolutely delighted. Gets there with an elegant cover drive. It is full and on off, it is hit through covers for three.
A dot to end! On off, defended.
A little bit of swing for Anderson! Fuller and outside off, shaping away. Left alone.
Another away swinger, this is also outside off though. Not played at.
Makes the batter play this time by bowling it on middle, it is pushed to mid on.
Better from James Anderson! Length and on off, hint of away movment. Defended nicely by Mitchell.
Another one outside off, not played at.
On off, DM pushes it to covers.
Blundell now moves to 94! Angled into the pads, this is worked towards square leg for one.
FOUR! The outfield is still really fast despite the rain! Fuller and around off, Mitchell looks to push at it, this one squirts off the outer half through point for a boundary.
Outside off, left alone.
Angled into the pads, Daryl works it through square leg and gets to the other end.
Fuller on off, this is defended.
Length ball on middle, Tom Blundell eases it towards the mid-wicket region.
Good-length delivery on off, Daryl Mitchell guides it towards backward point for a brace.
Sticks it his line and length, Daryl Mitchell defends it towards gully and gets a quick single.
On a good length and outside off, Tom Blundell looks to defend it but misses.
Goes fuller this time and on middle, Tom Blundell flicks it towards square leg.
On middle, defended towards mid on.
Touch fuller and on off, Tom Blundell is very solid in his defense.
On middle, this is pushed to mid on.
Good length and on off, kept out.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! There is the wicket England needed! The second new ball has done the trick for the hosts. End of an outstanding innings though from Daryl Mitchell! He walks off to a standing ovation. A beauty to get rid of him and a top delivery was needed. This is on a length and around off, it lands and moves away. Daryl Mitchell looks to defend but does so inside the line, it goes off the outside edge and it is taken by the keeper. Can England build on this?
Howout: c Ben Foakes b Stuart Broad

Commentary: OUT! RUN OUT! Colin is short! Two in two for England and they will feel they are right back into this one. That is poor from Colin, he was probably worried about the appeal. This is angled into the pads. Colin looks to flick but misses. It hits the pad and rolls towards the Pope at gully. Colin takes a few steps down the track and then turns in a lazy manner. Pope hits the stumps at the keeper's end and England start celebrating. It is taken upstairs and replays show Colin de Grandhomme is short.
Howout: run out (Ollie Pope)

Commentary: OUT! TIMBER! Three in three for England and the game has turned on its head. What a delivery again by Broad. The second new ball is doing wonders for the hosts. This is on a length and around off, this lands and jags back in. Kyle Jamieson looks to defend but is a little late on the shot. It hits the pad and then onto the off pole. New Zealand's lead is still 8 short of 250. The crowd here is delighted.
Howout: b Stuart Broad

Commentary: Played out! On middle, this is pushed back to the bowler. End of an over with three wickets in it.
LEG BYES! Tom Blundell remains on 94! Angled into the pads, Blundell looks to flick but misses, it hits the pad and goes down to fine leg for three.
Good length and on off, Southee pushes it to covers.
How do you play those! This seems like it is coming in with the angle, it lands and then moves away, also stays low. Southee is beaten as he tries to defend.
BEATEN AGAIN! Length and outside off, Southee initially pokes at it but then at the end pulls his bat back. It goes just past the outside edge.
Southee gets off the strike with one ball to go in the over! On middle, this is nudged on the leg side for one.
A dot to end which means Southee will be on strike! Shorter and on off, this is pushed to covers.
On a length and on middle, this is pushed back to the bowler.
Southee goes short. This one comes slow off the surface. Southee looks to pull but misses to get hit on the body.
Good length and on off, defended.

FOUR! The lead is not 250! A boundary off a leading edge. Angled into the pads, Southee looks to flick but it goes off the leading edge over mid off. The fielder hares after it, dives but fails to push it back in. Should have done better.
FOUR! Nice and fine! Consecutive boundaries! Short and on the body, this is pulled down to the fine leg fence.
That is a beauty! Length and on off, this lands and moves away. Southee is beaten as he tries to push at it. End of a good over though for New Zealand.
Two more! Angled into the pads, Tom works it through square leg for a couple. He is a boundary away now.

OUT! THREE REDS AND IS HEART BREAK FOR Tom Blundell! He falls 4 short of a ton! The inswinger does the trick for Anderson and New Zealand have lost 4 in no time. This is a length ball, it comes back in from outside off. It seams in late. Blundell lunges to defend but does so outside the line. He gets hit on the front pad. An appeal and the finger is raised. It is reviewed but more in hope. Replays show no bat and then three reds. An outstanding innings from him. Have to feel for him, a lot went on after he got into the 90s and in the end, he misses out on a well-deserved ton.
Howout: lbw b James Anderson

Commentary: England have their tails up here! On the pads, Patel looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. An appeal but turned down.
Good length and on middle, defended.
Good length and on off, Patel defends it out.
On middle, length, Patel gets right behind the line and keeps it out.
FOUR! This is how Southee is going to play an rightly so. Vital runs these for the Kiwis! On middle, this is lofted over the mid on fielder for a boundary. Not off the middle but hit well enough.
FOUR! JUST WIDE! Consecutive boundaries! Broad goes fuller this time, on middle, this is lofted past the diving mid on fielder and into the fence.
Fuller and angling into the pads, Southee works it to mid-wicket. Bairstow hurts his finger as he tries to stop the ball. Goes into the dressing room.
Swing and a miss! Angled into the pads, Southee looks to go over the leg side but misses.
Edgy run! Southee wanted a single! A low full toss outside off, Southee looks to drive, this goes off the toe-end down towards third man for one. Ajaz Patel has one ball to face in this over.
He survives! Outside off, left alone.
Goes short and down the leg side, left alone.
Outside off, this is hit through covers for one.
On middle, defended.
Drop and run and Ajaz Patel is off the mark! On off, this is pushed towards cover for one.
Short and on middle again, evaded.
A dot to end! On middle, kept out.
Tossed up on off, Patel drops it towards cover for one.
Slightly shorter and on middle, this is pushed down to long on for one.
Two more! A full toss on the pads, Patel paddle sweeps it towards fine leg and takes a brace.
This is very wide outside off, Patel looks to cut but misses.
Flatter and outside off, left alone.
How did that miss the off pole! This is tossed up around off, it drifts away and then turns back in after it lands. Ajaz Patel plays down the wrong line, he misses and it goes just past the off pole.
Outside off, left alone.
Fuller and on middle, Southee swings, it goes off the inner half through mid-wicket for one.

OUT! THREE REDS! Patel walks back and takes a review along with him! Not sure where that shot came from. He was probably tired of defending! On middle, Patel looks to heave it over the leg side but misses. It hits the back pad. An appeal and the finger is raised. Patel reviews but in vain. The move to get Potts on works. New Zealand lead by 272.
Howout: lbw b Matthew Potts

Commentary: Goes shorter and on middle, Trent Boult ducks under it.
Shorter one again, Trent Boult ducks again and lets it through towards the keeper.
FOUR! Bang! Length ball and outside off, Trent Boult drives it through long on for a boundary.
Tossed up outside off, Tim Southee hits it but straight towards the bowler.
This is wide outside off, Tim Southee drives straight towards the fielder at covers.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Matt Parkinson GETS HIS FIRST TEST WICKET! A special moment for him, he has been travelling with the English side for a sometime now, he really had to wait for his chance and now finally has a Test scalp. Tosses it up and bowls it wide outside off. Southee looks to hit it through covers, it goes off the outside edge and it is taken at first slip by Root! NEW ZEALAND HAVE BEEN BOWLED OUT FOR 285!
Howout: c Joe Root b Matt Parkinson

Commentary: Starts with a length ball outside off, Alex Lees leaves it alone.
FOUR! Fuller one outside off, Alex Lees gets on his knees and drives it through extra covers for a boundary. This was effortless from Alex Lees.
Length ball outside off, this is defended towards covers.
On a good length and outside off, Alex Lees leaves it alone.
Goes fuller and wide outside off, Alex Lees puts his bat across and eases it to point.
Outside off again, Alex Lees doesn't bother it.

Shorter and down the leg side. Root evades it.
On off, Root pushes it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Almost drags it on! 200 up for England. Just the 77 needed! Shorter and outside off, Root looks to cut, it goes off the underedge, past the off pole and down to the fine leg fence.
Fuller and on off, Root comes down the track and looks to flick but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Close! Outside off, once again comes back in but not enough to make the batter play.
On middle, Foakes plays it to mid on.
On off, defended.
On middle, this is clipped to mid-wicket.
Shorter and around off, Foakes evades it.
Two leg byes! On the pads, Foakes looks to flick, misses, it hits the pad and goes behind. Two taken.
This is banged in short, on middle, Root pulls it through square leg for one.
Outside off, left alone.
On middle, Foakes plays it to mid on.
Goes wide of the crease and angles it into the off pole. Defended well.
Attacks the stumps again, Foakes keeps it out.

EDGED BUT SHORT! A run as there is a misfield! On a length and around off, Foakes looks to block, it goes off the outside edge, lands short of the slip fielder. He lets it through and a single is taken.
On off, this is kept out well.
From very wide of the crease. On a length and on off, kept out.
On off, defended well.
Two more! Leg byes signaled! On the pads, Foakes looks to flick, it goes off the pads, down towards fine leg. Two taken.
On off, Foakes plays it to covers.
Bangs it short and on middle, Foakes ducks under it.
Two more! Angled into the pads, Root clips it through square leg for two.
On middle, this is pushed to mid on.
Well played again! On the pads, this is clipped through square leg for two. Fifty-run stand up between the two. A very important one but still, a lot of work left.
Good length and around off, Root opens the face and guides it to point.
On middle, this is dropped towards point for one.
Shorter and on off, Ben stands tall and pushes it to mid off.
Well fielded! Length and on off, Root pushes it towards cover. The fielder dives to his left and stops it well.
Two more! On middle, this is worked through mid-wicket. Two taken. Only 64 needed.
Short ball, this is pulled, off the back foot through square leg for one.
That is a good short ball, on the body, Foakes evades it.
Another short ball, another pull shot, through square leg for one.
A single to end day's play! Short and on middle, this is pulled through square leg for one. THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 3!
Southee begins with a length ball around off, Root shuffles across and nudges it down to fine leg. Takes a single, looks for the second run but it's not on. 60 more.
Around off, on a good length, Foakes is on the back foot as he defends it on the leg side.
Southee is too straight with his line, Foakes clips it off his pads behind square leg and collects a couple of runs.
Back of a length, on off, defended from the back foot to the off side.
Southee goes wide of the crease and angles in a length ball around off, Ben Foakes hangs on the back foot and defends it back.
Keeps probing with a length delivery, close to off, Foakes is again watchful in defense as he blocks it from the crease. 58 needed more.
Boult straightaway begins from 'round the wicket angle. He serves it full and outside off, Root strides forward and pushes it defensively to covers.
This time the line is a little too far outside off, Root offers no shot.
Darts in a length ball on off, Root defends it from the back foot to the off side.
Fine shot! The length is a shade too full, outside off, Root leans forward and drives it behind square on the off side. He gets a couple of runs.
On a length and outside off, Root stays back and taps it down to gully.
Short in length and outside off, Root goes on the back foot and steers it past point and gets another brace. 54 needed more.
A gentle delivery, on a length around off and angling in, Ben gets across and helps it to short mid-wicket.

That's a firm drive down the ground! Fuller and around off, Foakes forces it towards mid on where Southee dives across to his left and takes the pace off the ball. It rolls behind and the batters take two. England are dealing in couples this morning.
Drifting down the leg side, Foakes gets across but fails to flick. It goes off his pads to fine leg and they take another two, this time as leg byes. 50 needed more.
Fraction short and on off, Foakes punches from the back foot but finds the cover-point fielder.
Solid in defense. Around off, on a length, Ben offers a dead bat.
In the zone outside off, an easy leave for Ben Foakes.
Lovely shot from Root, for another two. Short in length and around off, Root turns inside the crease and pulls it in front of square on the leg side.
Length and outside off, it's stroked through point for one.
Digs it in short, outside off, Fokaes stays back and plays it down to point. He lets out a big shout for 'no' as Root looks interested in a run.
Angling away from the batter, outside off and on a length, Ben Foakes doesn't flirt with it.
Close to off, on a length and angling away again, Foakes lunges and defends it with an angled bat to the off side.
Lands it on a length around leg, angling across, Foakes stays on the back foot and jams it down safely. 47 needed more.
Shortish and on off, Root moves back and drops it with gentle hands to mid-wicket. Calls for a run and gets it comfortably.
Outside off, left alone.
Hurls a length ball in the channel outside off, Foakes covers his stumps and shoulders arms.
Fullish and around off, Foakes drives it down the ground but finds mid off.
FOUR! Excellent shot. The length goes slightly short and outside off, Foakes eases himself on the back foot and packs a punch through point for a glorious boundary. 42 needed more.

Vital stop with no third man in place. Around off, on a length, Ben plays late at it and guides it towards third man. Tom Latham immediately moves across to his right from second slip, dives and saves a certain boundary.
On a length and around middle, Root gets back and plays late but still finds gully.
Short in length, around leg, Root turns inside the crease and pulls it down to fine leg for one.
Bouncer to Foakes, around middle and leg, he ducks easily.
A near-yorker on off, Foakes brings his bat down in time and digs it out back towards the bowler.
Back of a length, around leg and middle, Ben glances it through square leg and picks up a single.
Fine shot for nothing! Fuller in length and outside off, Root plays an eye-catching cover drive but fails to find the gap. 40 more to win. England have added 21 runs in the 6 overs this morning.
Angles in a length ball on off, Foakes works it off his pads but fails to beat the diving short mid-wicket fielder.
FOUR! Pristine timing! Full in length and around off, Foakes shows the full face of his bat and  caresses it past the mid on fielder for a boundary.
Back of a length, around off, Ben goes on the back foot and taps it down to point. New Zealand are going through the motions with nothing happening off the pitch.
Bouncer around off, Ben Foakes picks it nice and early before ducking.
Finds the gap! It's on a length and outside off, Foakes leans forward, doesn't try to it hard, just pushes it with great timing through covers. Two more.
Slightly short in length and outside off, Foakes shoulders arms. 34 needed more.
Bowls it full but on the pads, Root whips it behind square leg and rotates the strike.
This one keeps a bit low from a length around off, Foakes stays focused and defends it out safely on the leg side.
Shortish and outside off, Ben cuts from the crease but finds point.
Around off, on a length, Foakes defends it solidly from the back foot.
A little bit of movement on this delivery. Full and around off, Foakes tries to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Pitches it up and around off, Foakes drives but finds the mid off fielder.
A touch short and around off, Root plays nice and late, from the back foot but it goes straight to the fielder at gully.
FOUR! Fantastic straight drive, this time from the blade of Root. Fullish and around off, Joe strides forward and strokes it elegantly down the ground for a boundary. Moves into the 90s.
Picks out gully. Short in length and around off, Root leans back and tries to guide it down to third man but the gully fielder intervenes with a dive to make the stop.
Beaten this time! A bit short again, outside off and staying down, Root once more attempts to lean back and cut but gets beaten.
Delivers it on a length and outside off, from wide of the crease, Root gets behind and defends it to mid on.
Root is eyeing that gap between slips and gully but so far has failed to pierce it. On a length and outside off, Joe runs it down late but once again the gully fielder makes the stop.
Fuller in length and outside off, Foakes is on the front foot and defends it solidly. 29 more to win.

FOUR! Pulled and pulled well! Short in length and around middle, Ben Foakes immediately goes on the back foot to ride the bounce and pulls it with authority through square leg for a boundary. Foakes has looked very positive this morning, taking the pressure off Root.
Uses the angle of the bowler and works a length ball to mid-wicket.
Angling in from around off, a length ball, Foakes tucks it through backward square leg and takes one.

EDGY FOUR! Luck is with England. Root moves to 96. Short and outside off, Root rocks back to cut but it nips back down the hill, takes the inside edge, beats the stumps and keeper. It scoots down to fine leg for a boundary.
Full and on middle, flicked behind square leg for a run. 19 more for a win, Root three away from a century and New Zealand are 5 overs away from the new ball.
Lands it on a length and outside off, Root gets across and tucks it through mid-wicket for one. The century stand comes up!
On a length and outside off, going straight on, Foakes has nothing to do.
Serves it on a length and outside off, Ben commits himself forward and defends it carefully towards gully.
Around off, on a length, Foakes gets back to work it on the leg side but it takes a soft leading edge and rolls to covers.
Delivers it outside off, Foakes plays it down from the back foot to gully.
Short and on off, Foakes pulls it through square leg for a couple. 16 needed more.
Serves it on a good length and outside off, Root stays on the back foot and taps it down to gully.
Serves it around off, angling in, Root forces it from the back foot to covers.

HUNDRED FOR ROOT! What a knock under pressure from the former England skipper! This will be one of those satisfying knocks as a batter! Always special when it comes while batting last in a Test match and in a winning cause. 26th Test hundred for Joe and he also completes 10000 Test runs. The Lord's goes Roooooooooooo... What a player!!! Fuller in length and around middle, Root clips it to deep mid-wicket and scampers back for the second run. Off goes the helmet and here comes the applause. This is his first Test ton in the fourth innings. 14 needed more.
Fuller and on off, defended back.
Full and around off, angling in, Joe gets forward and pushes it to mid on.
Movement in the air and off the pitch too as it lands on a fuller length, around middle, Root inside-edges his attempted flick shot down to fine leg. A single taken.
Boult returns to bowl again. Delivers it on a length around leg, it's worked behind square leg for a single.
Back of a length, on off and angling away, Foakes gets across the stumps and glances it to deep square leg for another run.
Pitches it up and around middle, Root drives it down to mid off.
Gets behind the line of the delivery and blocks it to covers.
Fuller and on middle, it's driven back towards the bowler.
A low full toss outside off, Root reaches out and strokes it to deep cover for a single.
FOUR! Finds the gap at last! A touch short in length and outside off, Root stays on the back foot and delicately guides it through the gap between gully and wide slip for a boundary.
FOUR! Root is in a hurry, two more needed! This one is full and outside off, Root presses forward and creams his drive through mid off.
Almost drags it on! Southee gets a length ball to bend back in down the slope, Root sticks back to cut but it takes the bottom edge and goes on the bounce to the keeper.
Width there, short and outside off, Root strokes it through the line but the point fielder makes a diving stop.

FOUR! Here is the winning shot! Joe Root has done it. New era, new England, a new captain and they start with a thumping win over New Zealand. Back of a length, around off, Root goes back and smacks it over mid-wicket for a boundary. Root jumps in delight and the English balcony is on its feet. ENGLAND WIN BY 5 WICKETS!
